Tigwi is a microblogging website designed to work on Windows Azure.

Dependencies :
- MSBuild Community Tasks

To connect to Azure, you will need a file named ConnectionInfo.xml placed at the root of the project (same directory as the README file) which looks like this: (To complete with your connection informations)

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<Project ToolsVersion="4.0" xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/developer/msbuild/2003">
	<PropertyGroup>
		<AzureSubscriptionID></AzureSubscriptionID>
		<AzureCertificateThumbprint></AzureCertificateThumbprint>
		<AzureHostedServiceName></AzureHostedServiceName>
		<AzureStorageAccountName></AzureStorageAccountName>
		<AzureStorageAccountKey></AzureStorageAccountKey>	
	</PropertyGroup>
	<ItemGroup>
		<!-- Comment the next line to use storage emulator on your local machine -->
		<ConnectionFiles Include="ServiceConfiguration.Local.cscfg" />
		<ConnectionFiles Include="ServiceConfiguration.Cloud.cscfg" />
	</ItemGroup>
</Project>

Warning : For this method to work, you must use ConnectionString.
Warning : In case the build fails, your keys will be hardcoded.
